# Svelte Counter Component

Here's a simple counter component:

```svelte
<script>
  let count = 0;

  function increment() {
    count++;
  }

  function decrement() {
    count--;
  }

  function reset() {
    count = 0;
  }
</script>

<div class="counter">
  <h1>Count: {count}</h1>

  <div class="buttons">
    <button on:click={decrement}>-</button>
    <button on:click={increment}>+</button>
    <button on:click={reset}>Reset</button>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .counter {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 2rem;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 3rem;
    color: #333;
  }

  .buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  button {
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    background-color: #007bff;
    color: white;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background-color 0.2s;
  }

  button:hover {
    background-color: #0056b3;
  }

  button:active {
    transform: scale(0.98);
  }
</style>
```

## Using the Component

```svelte
<script>
  import Counter from './Counter.svelte';
</script>

<Counter />
```

## Advanced Version with Props

If you want to make it more reusable:

```svelte
<script>
  export let initialValue = 0;
  export let step = 1;

  let count = initialValue;

  function increment() {
    count += step;
  }

  function decrement() {
    count -= step;
  }

  function reset() {
    count = initialValue;
  }
</script>

<div class="counter">
  <h1>Count: {count}</h1>

  <div class="buttons">
    <button on:click={decrement}>- {step}</button>
    <button on:click={increment}>+ {step}</button>
    <button on:click={reset}>Reset</button>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  /* ... same styles as above ... */
</style>
```

## Usage with Props

```svelte
<Counter initialValue={10} step={5} />
```

**Key Features:**
- ✅ Reactive state with `let count`
- ✅ Click handlers with `on:click`
- ✅ Scoped styling
- ✅ Optional props for customization
- ✅ Simple and beginner-friendly

